Document: Canvas Layers
Path: godot/tutorials/2d/canvas_layers.rst
Summary: This section explains how to use Canvas Layers for organizing 2D UI elements in Godot.

Canvas Layers allow you to organize 2D UI elements into separate layers for better management. Each CanvasLayer node acts as a container that can be positioned independently of other layers. This is particularly useful for separating UI elements like menus, HUDs, and overlays. To create a Canvas Layer, add a CanvasLayer node as a child of the CanvasItem node. You can adjust the layer's position, scale, and rotation independently of other layers. Multiple CanvasLayer nodes can be used to group related UI elements together. This system helps maintain clean scene hierarchies and simplifies transformations for complex UI layouts.
